  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nFiggy Frogwich\nFood Info\n25\n20\n5\nMeat\nObject Info\n15 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x2\n20 sec\n1\nMiscellaneous\n\"frognewton\"\n“The fig really brings it all together.”\n–Wilson\n“All that fig almost masks the frog flavor.”\n–Willow\n“Is sweet, but also slimy.”\n–Wolfgang\n“Sweet and only a little slimy.”\n–Wendy\n“READY FOR CONSUMPTION”\n–WX-78\n“It has quite a unique flavor.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“The fig masks the swamp taste.”\n–Woodie\n“This recipe has legs.”\n–Maxwell\n“Intö my belly with ye!”\n–Wigfrid\n“Something we both like!”\n–Webber\n“A lesser known French recipe.”\n–Warly\n“Squishy”\n–Wormwood\n“Surprisingly tasty.”\n–Winona\n“How do the mortals come up with these things?”\n–Wortox\n“Glurph! There frog leg in this!”\n–Wurt\n“Hey, that's pretty good! What's in it?”\n–Walter\n“It's very flavorful.”\n–Wanda\nFiggy Frogwich is a Meat Food item exclusive to Don't Starve Together and introduced in the Waterlogged beta. Consuming it will increase the player's body temperature by 1 degree per second in 15 seconds.\nAdding a Vegetable has a 50% chance to result in a Froggle Bunwich. Adding Honey results in Honey Nuggets. Using only one Twig will result in Kabobs. Adding one Twig and any piece of Meat (besides a Barnacle) will result in Figkababs. Using any Egg and a Vegetable will result in Pierogi. Using a Barnacle and a Vegetable will result in Barnacle Pita.\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\nExamples[edit | edit source]\nThe most economical recipe\n50% Chance to result in Froggle Bunwich\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
